B.S8=new A.K(B.xm,["Current","Apr.2023","Young Platform","Turin, Italy","\u2022 Building the italian main cryptocurrencies Exchange.\n\u2022 Started working on a production-ready released project. This required adapting and engaging with already established flows, while improving the standards at the same time.\n\u2022 Worked on entry-point features like the authentication process and the onboarding.\n \u2022 With the team we took care of payment related features, contract registrations and direct-debt payment.","Current","Sep.2021","Master's degree in Software engineering\nPolitecnico di Torino","Turin, Italy","Jan.2023","Sep.2021","AliraHealth","Remote","\u2022 Worked on a digital health product in Scrum, from creation to release, using cutting-edge technologies.\n\u2022 Built 2 frontend applications, 1 mobile and 1 web, both in Flutterwith shared custom packages, design system and core functionalities.\n\u2022 Worked on 2 Go microservices to gather data with gRPC and expose them via GraphQL APIs.\n\u2022 Worked closely with product team, addressed regular production bugs, improvements and discuss about requirements.","Oct.2021","Dic.2020","Starty","Remote","\u2022 Worked with a small team on a startup product, in the fintech field.\n\u2022 Build 1 mobile application in Flutter and partially operate the Firebase backend.\n\u2022 Actively participate in the team\u2019s discussions on startup technical decisions.","Sep.2021","Sep.2017","Bachelor's degree in computer engineering\nPolitecnico di Torino","Turin, Italy","Sep.2017","Jul.2016","MDPtech","Manta, Italy","\u2022 First experience as developer, in a small local company.\n\u2022 Built multiple Android applications to comunicate with industrial machines using the smartphone\u2019s Bluetooth low energy.\n\u2022 Interacted with physical/electrial components, warehouse and clients.","2016","","IT technical diploma\nI.I.S. G.Vallauri","Fossano, Italy","From","to"],t.w)
